==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Drysalter
<hw>Dry"salt`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dealer in salted
or dried meats, pickles, sauces, etc., and in the materials used in
pickling, salting, and preserving various kinds of food Hence drysalters
usually sell a number of saline substances and miscellaneous
drugs.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

